---
/**
 * /about — Founder introduction. Trust-loop sibling to /principles.
 *
 * IA per meta/specs/pages/about.md §4 and meta/compositions/pages/about.md §2.
 * Copy verbatim from meta/content/drafts/pages/about.md (Approved 2026-05-18).
 *
 * Composition verdict (ii): page skips <Hero> entirely. Eyebrow + lede are
 * site-side prose elements using DS tokens. Single <h1> at the top of section
 * 1 ("The arc"); sections 2 and 3 are <h2>. Zero motion, zero client JS.
 * See meta/compositions/pages/about.md §2 Section 2 (verdict justification)
 * and §6.1 (DS-gap proposal filed forward — not blocking v1).
 *
 * Decisions honoured:
 *   A4  — four-item nav: Why AI → Roles → Principles → About
 *   A5  — explicit first person throughout sections 1 and 2
 *   A7  — section 3 opens with R27 verbatim; ~80 words; brand-voice declarative
 *   A9  — no <h1> in hero region; <h1> moves to section 1 ("The arc")
 *   A11 — /principles-style brand-voice end-CTA; differentiated wording
 *   A12 — Instrument Serif italic section headings, ≤3 words each
 *   A14 — <title> "About — pouk.ai"; meta description brand-voice; ≤155 chars
 *   A15 — standalone Person JSON-LD; no worksFor; no sameAs
 *
 * Voice-shift documentation (spec §5 locked shifts):
 *   §3 Pouākai — first-person body → brand-voice declarative (A7)
 *   End CTA    — first-person body → brand-voice / second-person invitational (A11)
 *   Meta       — first-person body → brand-voice declarative (A14)
 *   These shifts are spec-locked; future revisions may NOT normalize them.
 *
 * Atomic migration: Pouākai sentence removed from HomeHero.tsx (R14 + R27 closed).
 */

import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "About — pouk.ai";
const pageDescription =
  "pouk.ai is one operator. Frontend engineering background, now running technical consulting through the AI tools that collapse months into days.";
const canonical = "https://pouk.ai/about";

/**
 * Standalone Person JSON-LD — spec §6 / A15b.
 * No worksFor relation. No sameAs block (no social URLs in structured data).
 */
const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  name: "Arian Zargaran",
  jobTitle: "Founder, pouk.ai",
  url: "https://pouk.ai/about",
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  canonical={canonical}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  currentRoute="/about"
>
  <div class="site-page">

    <!--
      Hero region — eyebrow + lede, NO <Hero> molecule, NO <h1>.
      Composition verdict (ii): /about skips <Hero> entirely.
      Two prose elements only; the page's single <h1> lives in section 1 below.
      See meta/compositions/pages/about.md §2 Section 2.
    -->
    <div class="about-eyebrow-band">
      <!-- Eyebrow: page label. <p> not <h1>/<h2> — no heading role here. -->
      <p class="about-eyebrow">About</p>
      <!--
        Hero lede — 1 sentence, second-person, 12 words.
        Copy: meta/content/drafts/pages/about.md §2 heroLede (Q3 ratified).
      -->
      <p class="about-lede">Who you&rsquo;d be writing into if you sent the email below.</p>
    </div>

    <!--
      Section 1 — "The arc"
      The page's single <h1>. First-person throughout (A5).
      ~165 words across three paragraphs; third paragraph is a single
      load-bearing sentence.
      Copy: meta/content/drafts/pages/about.md §2 section1.
    -->
    <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="arc">
      <h1 id="arc" class="about-section-heading">The arc</h1>
      <div class="about-body">
        <p>
          I came up writing frontend code &mdash; building interfaces, shipping
          product, sitting close enough to engineering decisions to learn which
          ones held up and which ones rotted in six months. The conversations on
          those teams kept turning toward AI, first as a curiosity, then as a
          tool people were quietly using to do parts of their job, then as a
          question the engineering org couldn&rsquo;t answer on its own: where
          does this actually go in production?
        </p>
        <p>
          I stopped writing frontend full-time to answer that question for the
          teams asking it. pouk.ai is what I do now &mdash; technical consulting
          for operators who&rsquo;d rather ship something they can measure than
          commission a report on what they might build. I take a small number of
          engagements at a time. I write the code I recommend. I leave behind
          systems an in-house team can run, not slide decks that need
          translation.
        </p>
        <p>
          When you email <a href="mailto:hello@pouk.ai">hello@pouk.ai</a>, I am
          the person who replies.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!--
      Section 2 — "Why pouk.ai"
      <h2> (semantic; same visual weight as section 1 h1 — composition §3).
      First-person, founding-posture, autobiographical only (A10).
      ~175 words. No competitive language, no stance slogans.
      Copy: meta/content/drafts/pages/about.md §2 section2.
    -->
    <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="why">
      <h2 id="why" class="about-section-heading">Why pouk.ai</h2>
      <div class="about-body">
        <p>
          The reason I started pouk.ai instead of going back to a staff
          engineering role is that the tools changed underneath me. The same
          modern AI tools that show up in every founder&rsquo;s Twitter feed
          &mdash; the ones the press keeps calling transformative &mdash;
          actually do the boring thing they claim to do, when an engineer holds
          them correctly. They collapse what used to take a dev team six months
          into days, sometimes weeks for the harder parts. I watched this happen
          on projects I was on and projects I wasn&rsquo;t.
        </p>
        <p>
          The work that follows from that is specific. Most teams don&rsquo;t
          need a strategy retreat about AI; they need someone who has already
          wired these tools into a production codebase and can do it again on
          theirs. That is the seam pouk.ai operates in. I take on the build, the
          automation, or the advisory engagement that gets a team across the gap
          between &ldquo;we should be doing something with AI&rdquo; and
          &ldquo;we are running this in production this quarter.&rdquo;
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!--
      Section 3 — "Pouākai"
      <h2>. Brand-voice declarative (NOT first-person) — A7 voice-shift locked.
      ~75 words, three sentences.
      Sentence 1: R27 verbatim migration from / lede (atomic migration closes R14 + R27).
      Sentence 2: Māori source acknowledgment.
      Sentence 3: respect posture — no visual motifs, no cultural claim.
      Copy: meta/content/drafts/pages/about.md §2 section3.
      VOICE-SHIFT NOTE: this section is brand-voice declarative, not first-person.
      Do NOT normalize to first-person on future revision (spec §5 locked shift).
    -->
    <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="poukai">
      <!--
        Pouākai: macron rendered via literal Unicode character (U+0101).
        HTML entity equivalent: &#257; — either form is acceptable per composition §5.
      -->
      <h2 id="poukai" class="about-section-heading">Pou&#257;kai</h2>
      <div class="about-body">
        <p>
          Named for Pou&#257;kai &mdash; the largest eagle that ever flew,
          hunting by stooping from height. The name comes from M&#257;ori
          tradition; the bird is real, extinct for around six hundred years, and
          the spelling carries the macron it was given. pouk.ai borrows the name
          as a reference point &mdash; a hunter that worked by altitude and
          timing &mdash; and stops there: no M&#257;ori visual motifs in the
          brand, no claim to the culture, no metaphor stretched past the
          one-line origin.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!--
      End CTA — single muted line, brand-voice / second-person invitational.
      Shape: /principles-style conditional ("If <condition>, <address>").
      Noun: "the inbox" — unique to /about; closes the loop on the hero lede.
      VOICE-SHIFT NOTE: body first-person → CTA brand-voice / second-person.
      Do NOT normalize (spec §5 locked shift).
      Copy: meta/content/drafts/pages/about.md §2 endCta (Q2 ratified).
    -->
    <div class="about-end-cta">
      <p>
        If the inbox sounds right,{" "}
        <a href="mailto:hello@pouk.ai">hello@pouk.ai</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
